    "Body": " Staff HCM Cloud Consultant, Functional ArcLight Consulting - Burlington, MA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $69,000 - $100,000 a year Benefits Cell Phone Reimbursement Internet Reimbursement Health Insurance Vision Insurance Flexible Schedule Qualifications Quality Assurance Project Management Communication Skills Human Resources Microsoft Powerpoint Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description As a Staff Consultant, you will have the opportunity to work with leading firms across all major industrial sectors including healthcare, financial services, pharmaceutical, biotech, education, manufacturing, communications, beverage and foodservice, and many more industries! Careers at ArcLight offer advancement opportunities, competitive benefits, volunteer programs, 401(k) plans, and flexible work hours. ArcLight operates out of Woburn, MA, easily accessible via Public Transportation and near many major cities. Skills You Acquire at ArcLight: Consulting Skills: Become an expert with Oracle applications and facilitate our clients\u2019 transitions from legacy technologies to Oracle\u2019s best-in-class HCM platforms. In the course of your project work and our development programs, you\u2019ll acquire the research, client relations, problem solving, presentation, project management, and information technology skills that are the foundation of many successful consulting careers. Cloud Technology Applications: ArcLight offers the unique opportunity for candidates to learn and implement Oracle\u2019s innovative new product, the HCM Cloud. Oracle\u2019s HCM offerings support Benefits Management, Compensation Management, Payroll Processing, Talent Management and other essential elements of strategic human resources management. Oracle\u2019s Cloud offerings leverage the technologies accelerating modern business including Big Data Analytics, AI, Blockchain and others. Analytical Capabilities: Throughout the implementation cycle for HCM deployments, ArcLight consultants are challenged to break down and clarify difficult concepts for customers and \u2018dig in\u2019 and build out Oracle\u2019s Cloud modules. As you design, test and implement Oracle\u2019s Cloud solutions, considerations of the potential downstream impacts of decisions ensure the capabilities you\u2019ve designed and delivered are robust, sustainable, and readily adaptable to future needs. Process Improvement: Work with peers to continuously improve ArcLight\u2019s delivery methodologies and tools. Contribute to enhancing ArcLight\u2019s value proposition for clients through process efficiencies, design excellence, quality assurance and deep functional and technical knowledge. Benefits & Career Advancement: Competitive compensation structure (top of market) Quarterly / Annual bonus program rewarding individual efforts and company progress Medical, Dental, Vision coverage 401(k) retirement plan Life insurance benefits Volunteer Time allowance Cell Phone and internet reimbursement Charitable contribution program 3 Weeks PTO program Floating holidays / Company holidays Qualifications: 0-2 years of experience Knowledge of HR processes preferred Interpersonal, communication and presentation skills Self-motivated and able to plan work effort and manage priorities Keen attention to detail Intermediate to expert level excel skills. PowerPoint / Word experience a plus. Strong academic performance Willing to learn a range of business or technical specialties based on business needs Demonstrated ability to convey complex information in a clear and concise manner Requirements: Bachelor\u2019s degree in Business, Human Resources, Computer Science, or related field, or its equivalent. Willing to travel as needed. This position is not eligible for visa sponsorship ", 
